Aim: Perform Remote login using Telnet Server.

Hardware/Software required: Telnet Server

Step 1: Open Terminal
Press: Ctrl + Alt + T

Step 2: Install Telnet Server
Type the following command and press Enter: 
sudo apt-get install telnetd

Step 3: Enter Password and Confirm Installation
You will be asked: “Do you want to continue? [Y/n]” Type 'y' and press Enter. Wait for installation to complete.

Step 4: Restart the inetd Service
Type this command and press Enter: 
sudo /etc/init.d/openbsd-inetd restart

Step 5: Check if Telnet Server is Running
Type: 
sudo netstat -tnlp | grep telnet

Step 6: Test Telnet Connection (Localhost)
On the same machine, type:
telnet 127.0.0.1

Step 7: Login to the Shell via Telnet
You will be asked to login: 
- Enter your Ubuntu username 
- Enter your password
